#5836
Amidst the Sand Dunes~
The dry desolate desert, dotted with empty sand dunes, stretches out all
around.  Here and there, small patches of tall green grass can be seen
growing fight off the deadly environments.  From time to time, the wind
blows by, picking up the fine granules of yellow sand and throwing them into
the air.  A path made of irregularly shaped slabs of sandstone, which have
been made smooth on top, can barely be seen under the thin blanket of sand. 
The path measures roughly a twenty cubits across, and leads south towards
more dunes.  
