#5837
The Solar Gates~
The wind worn road narrows, and a group of ruined structures can be seen
farther south.  Two colossal sandstone columns, measuring eighty cubits high
and fifty cubits apart, stand at the end of the path and are joined by an
arch of the same material.  From the base to the crown, the columns are
covered by rows of once intricately chiseled glyphs, but many of them are
now worn away by the sharp lashing of the desert winds.  A golden statue of
a phoenix perches on the arch, its wings spread out.  The feathers are made
so that they focus the sunlight during the day onto the circular area before
the gates.  The road continues south through the gates and north back
towards the sand dunes.  
