#5840
Solar Confluence~
A white round dais occupies the centre of the square, and it is
featureless save for an ominous pit at its centre that seems to give off
negative energy.  An obelisk once stood over the pit, but now it lies split
cleanly in half on either side of the pit: one half points in the direction
of the rising sun, while the other the direction of the setting sun. 
Powerful runes have been carved into the surface of the obelisk, and even
though they have also been split, they still glow with magical energy.  A
silent pyramid lies further to the south, while the statue lined path lies
to the north.  
