#5841
The Well of Light~
The road leading south from the Solar Confluence is paved with finely
carved golden blocks of sunstone, and each bears a single rune.  Only a few
of the many rune covered colonnades that once flanked this path remain
standing while the rest lie in ruins.  At the centre of the path lies a star
shaped well, which measured around fifteen cubits across.  A small brazier
sits at each of the eight vertex of the well, and they are lit with an ugly
red glow.  The well has long dried up and is now only filled with the yellow
sands of the desert.  To the north lies the strangely sinister Solar Square,
while the collapsed gates of the pyramid lie to the south.  
