The Morning Road~
White quartzes are set in the form of sunbursts amidst the yellow
sandstone road.  The once beautiful design is now covered with running
cracks and deformed depressions.  To the side of the road, dead tree trunks
can be seen, their dry gnarled limbs reaching up at the sky as if in fury. 
The road stretches nearly a score cubits in length, and at its western end
lies a lone structure.  
