#5844
Ruined Temple~
The ruined structure is once the house dedicated to the rising sun, for
it faces the east.  Semi-circular steps lead up to the entrance of the
building, which lies buried within an impenetrable layer of desert sand. 
The dry raging wind of the desert blows strongly from the east depositing
even more sand on the mound.  The windborne sand has heavily eroded the
house, and its corners have been made almost round.  Four pillars, which
must have once held flames on their peaks, flank the four sided structure. 
The Morning Road leads back eastwards to the main road.  
